						<summary>

						<p>This records a similar gift of 12(1/2) <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold with which to by 96 sheep and a ram for burning a lamp in the temple, by Araiyaṉ Vēṅgaḍavaṉ of the <hi rend="bold">Mūttavāḻpeṟṟa-Kaikkōḷar</hi> (regiment). The significance of this term is not clear. Probably the regiment was so named for the experience in swordsmanship of its members.</p>						

						</summary>
